<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-05-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="319" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3419</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Group</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">New
                                        York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-05-18"><hi rend="italic">May 18,
                                1921</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received May 20.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: We received your letter of May 17th,<note n="55" xml:id="d319fn55">Not printed.</note> enclosing a copy of a
                            telegram from the Embassy at Paris of May 14th,<note n="56" xml:id="d319fn56"><hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi></note> transmitting
                            a message from Mr. Lamont regarding the proposed formation of a council
                            to consider Consortium matters.</p>
                        <p>The American Group met today and discussed this proposal, and we transmit
                            for your information copy of a telegram which we are despatching to Mr.
                                Lamont,<note n="55" xml:id="d319fn57">Not printed.</note> indicating
                            the approval of our Group as therein set forth.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully,</p>
                        <closer><hi rend="smallcaps">J. P. Morgan</hi> &amp; Co.<lb/><hi rend="italic">For the American Group</hi></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>